            sam bahadur
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Year:</strong> 2023</li>
                <li><strong>Main Actors:</strong> vicky kaushal,sanya malhotra,fatima sana shaikh and more</li>
                <li><strong>Description:</strong> Sam Manekshaw, known as Sam Bahadur, was an influential Indian Army officer and the first Field Marshal of India. He played a crucial role during the Indo-Pakistani War of 1971, which led to the creation of Bangladesh. His leadership and strategic acumen were pivotal in India's military successes. Manekshaw was celebrated for his charisma, wit, and straightforwardness. After his retirement, he became a prominent figure in Indian military history and is remembered for his contributions to the country.

                    Please verify any critical information for accuracy.</li>
